d ads, categories, restaurants, and...\",\n91:         \"`renderSearchBar` and `usesLocalSearchState()` keep only route-local query state without any preference persistence.\",\n92:         \"`renderSearchBar` feeds route-level query state into `HomeStore.buildFilteredState(...)` and `HistoryStore.buildVisibleState(...)`, enabling immediate home/history filtering from the shared search surface.\",\n93:         \"`buildHistoryRoute` reloads `HistoryStore.buildVisibleState(...)` on each route render so the current liked-restaurant state is reflected whenever the page is entered or updated.\",\n94:         \"`HistoryStore` plus `FoodikeBootstrap` route state expose observable search/tab state and reload the repository-backed favourites list on each rebuild.\",\n95:         \"`bootstrap_page.cj` keeps `homeSelectedFilter` in route state, and `buildFilterRow` re-renders selected styling while `HomeStore.buildFilteredState(...)` applies the active chip to visible lists.\",\n96:         \"`FoodikeBootstrap::buildHistoryRoute` binds current query/tab state and recomputes `HistoryStore.buildVisibleState(...)` whenever the history route is shown.\",\n97:         \"`HistoryPageState` and the route-local history state fields keep equivalent plain state for favourites, records, query, and tab selection without any permission handling.\"\n98:       ],\n99:       \"acceptanceEvidence\": [\n100:         \"Replace broad endpoints with precise target functions, types, resources, or tests before closing the group.\"\n101:       ],\n102:       \"riskHints\": [\n103:         \"current evidence uses broad shell/root/whole-file endpoints\"\n104:       ],\n105:       \"matrixRows\": [\n106:         {\n107:           \"kind\": \"source-feature\",\n108:           \"featureId\": \"app-src-main-java-com-example-foodike-presentation-home-ef0657c4ea-005-screen-lifecycle-entry-point-initializat\",\n109:           \"featureName\": \"Screen lifecycle, entry point initialization, resume/pause refres